metadata.name: Freedom Flower #1
metadata.description: The Freedom Flower is an image depicting the beauty and joy of the the Guldexw√Æn, or reverse tulip, whose gene center originates in Kurdistan. The flower's uniquely positioned petals are an adaptive feature that thrives as a source of color in the region's mountain landscapes. The Freedom Flower represents the essence and forbearance of the Kurdish people's intent to live in freedom.
